.TH VEK_COSINE_F32 3 "2024-01-01" "vek 0.8.0" "Library Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
vek_cosine_f32 \- cosine similarity between two f32 vectors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <vek.h>
.sp
.BI "float vek_cosine_f32(const float *" a ", const float *" b ", size_t " n ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR vek_cosine_f32 ()
computes the cosine similarity between two single-precision floating-point
vectors:
.PP
.RS
result = dot(a, b) / (||a|| * ||b||)
.RE
.PP
The result ranges from -1.0 (opposite) to 1.0 (identical), with 0.0
indicating orthogonality. If either vector has zero magnitude, the result
is undefined.
.SH PARAMETERS
.TP
.I a
First input vector. Must have at least
.I n
elements.
.TP
.I b
Second input vector. Must have at least
.I n
elements.
.TP
.I n
Number of elements. Must be greater than 0.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the cosine similarity as a single-precision float in the range
[-1.0, 1.0].
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
float a[] = {1.0f, 0.0f, 1.0f};
float b[] = {1.0f, 1.0f, 0.0f};
float result = vek_cosine_f32(a, b, 3);  // 0.5
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vek_dot_f32 (3),
.BR vek_l2sq_f32 (3),
.BR vek_cosine_i8 (3)
